where dim is the within-module node degree and di is the overall network degree for a node I29. Within-module nodes with different levels of participation in connections with nodes in other modules were classified as follows: P < 0.05 are ultra-peripheral, 0.05 < P < 0.62 are peripheral nodes, 0.62 < P < 0.80 are non-hub connectors, and P > 0.80 are non-hub kinless29.
